!           new Attribute(&amp;quot;text-decoration&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;none&amp;quot;, false);&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;public static final Attribute TEXT_INDENT =&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;new Attribute(&amp;quot;text-indent&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;0&amp;quot;, true);&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;public static final Attribute TEXT_TRANSFORM =&lt;br/&gt;
========&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Let me comment on it.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
156         public static final Attribute BACKGROUND_POSITION =&lt;br/&gt;
157             new Attribute(&amp;quot;background-position&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;0% 0%&amp;quot;, false);&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This part is harmless.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
304         public static final Attribute TEXT_DECORATION =&lt;br/&gt;
305             new Attribute(&amp;quot;text-decoration&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;none&amp;quot;, false);&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This part breaks us.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
CSS spec for the text-decoration:&lt;br/&gt;
----&lt;br/&gt;
This property is not inherited, but elements should match their parent. E.g., if&lt;br/&gt;
an element is underlined, the line should span the child elements. The color of&lt;br/&gt;
the underlining will remain the same even if descendant elements have different&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;#39;color&amp;#39; values.&lt;br/&gt;
----&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
We do not do any matching to parent. Thus children would not match the parent&lt;br/&gt;
text-decoration.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Try this for example:&lt;br/&gt;
---&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;head&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;STYLE TYPE=&amp;quot;text/css&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
BODY    {text-decoration:underline }&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/STYLE&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/head&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;body&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
test test &amp;lt;b&amp;gt;bold&amp;lt;/b&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/body&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/html&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
---&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Mozilla underlines everything. Swing-text currently underlines everything too.&lt;br/&gt;
After the suggested fix there is no underline.</comment>
